wiki.text:
'FEI' may refer to:
* Financial Executives International (FEI), an American organization for senior-
  level financial executives
* [[Fiscal Especial Independiente]], the special prosecutors of the government
  of Puerto Rico
* FEI Company, a supplier of electron microscopy tools
* International Federation for Equestrian Sports or Fédération Équestre
  Internationale, an international governing body of horse sports

'Fei' may refer to:
* Fei (letter) or פ, a letter in the Hebrew alphabet
* Fei (surname), a common Chinese surname
* Wang Feifei (王霏霏), stage name Fei, one of two Chinese singers in South Korean
  girl group Miss A
* Fei Comodo, a British post-hardcore band
* Fei County, in Shandong, China
